      <section class="section">
        <p class="section-label">Care model</p>
        <h2>Everything we do is connected</h2>
        <p class="section-intro">A child's placement is not just accommodation. It is a coordinated system of care, routine, relationships, safeguarding and therapeutic support.</p>
        <div class="grid three">
          <article class="card" id="therapeutic-care"><span class="number">1</span><h3>Therapeutic Residential Care</h3><p>PACE-informed and trauma-aware support helps children feel safe, understood and able to develop trust. Staff respond with playfulness, acceptance, curiosity and empathy.</p></article>
          <article class="card" id="staffing"><span class="number">2</span><h3>24/7 Staffing and 1:1 Ratio</h3><p>Our minimum 1:1 staffing ratio, waking night support and consistent routines help young people feel protected throughout the day and night.</p></article>
          <article class="card" id="education"><span class="number">3</span><h3>Education Support</h3><p>We support EHCPs, IEPs and PEPs, liaise with schools and encourage study routines that keep each child connected to learning.</p></article>
          <article class="card" id="health"><span class="number">4</span><h3>Health and Wellbeing</h3><p>Children are registered with local health services on admission. We support CAMHS collaboration, medication management and health education.</p></article>
          <article class="card" id="family-contact"><span class="number">5</span><h3>Family Contact and Relationships</h3><p>We facilitate and record family contact in line with the care plan, helping children maintain safe relationships that matter to them.</p></article>
          <article class="card" id="life-skills"><span class="number">6</span><h3>Life Skills and Independence</h3><p>Young people build practical skills through cooking, budgeting, community involvement, self-care and confidence-building routines.</p></article>
          <article class="card" id="safeguarding"><span class="number">7</span><h3>Safeguarding</h3><p>Safeguarding is woven through recruitment, supervision, risk assessment, documentation, training and daily practice.</p></article>
        </div>
      </section>
      <section class="band"><div class="section story-grid reverse"><div class="story-copy"><p class="section-label">Human care</p><h2>High standards, delivered in ordinary moments</h2><p>Therapeutic care happens during conversations, meals, school runs, difficult evenings and calm mornings. We use clear plans and professional systems, but the work is human at its core.</p><p>Children need adults who can hold boundaries without withdrawing warmth. That is the standard we train, supervise and support our team to meet.</p></div><figure class="image-panel"><img src="images/creative-children-painting-home-development-colorful-activity-fun-education-together-kids-drawing-learning-with-paper-bonding-future-artist-homework-with-art-project.webp" alt="Children painting together in a home learning activity" loading="lazy" /><figcaption class="image-caption">Therapeutic care in everyday routines</figcaption></figure></div></section>
      <section class="cta-band"><div class="cta-inner"><div><h2>Need to discuss a placement?</h2><p>Call us to talk through suitability, current availability and the referral process.</p></div><div class="section-actions"><a class="button invert" href="tel:+441184400118">Call 0118 440 0118</a><a class="button secondary" href="referrals.html">Referral process</a></div></div></section>
      <section class="section"><h2>Services: questions answered</h2><div class="faq-list"><details class="faq-item"><summary>What services does Animate Care provide?</summary><p>Animate Care provides therapeutic residential care, 24/7 staffing, education support, health and wellbeing support, family contact, life skills and safeguarding.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Does Animate Care support children with EBD?</summary><p>Yes. Animate Care supports children aged 8-17 with emotional and behavioural difficulties through trauma-aware, PACE-informed residential care.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Does Animate Care support education?</summary><p>Yes. We work with schools, local authorities and professionals on EHCPs, IEPs and PEPs.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Does Animate Care provide waking night support?</summary><p>Yes. Waking night staff provide supervision and support overnight.</p></details></div></section>
